love this concept... hope it stays yellow!

Is It Getting Better? is a kinetic sculpture changing its shape depending on the latest COVID-19 data received. The system interrogates an online data source once per day to collect the latest total number of cases and deaths in the UK. It then analyses the data to define if the % of increase is slowing down or not. If the number of cases is getting better, it shows yellow triangles, otherwise, it shows the black ones. The number of deaths is represented by a change of colour in the LED, from green to purple.⁠
⁠.⁠
The sculpture is made out of paper triangles, opening and closing with the movement of a servo motor hidden inside the box. Each triangle is attached to a string, then attached to a side of the servo. When the servo moves from 0 to 180 degrees, it closes the yellow triangles to open the black ones, and vice versa.⁠
⁠.⁠
Is It Getting Better? works as a simple data checker to indicate if the numbers are getting better or not. Its 2 states (good / bad) is a conscious decision to simplify the reading of the current data and go against the information overload that is served on the news and social media. If it stays in the yellow state for several days, one can hope that the decreasing phase of the bell curve has been reached.⁠
⁠.⁠
.⁠

√® sempre un piacere rivederli e quando mi presento davanti alla porta di casa mi fanno una grande festa, felici di avermi accanto.
Mi ha fatto pure piacere rivedere Jean-Paul, che mi ha salutato dalla finestra della cucina e mi ha detto di avere guardato il promo montato con l'intervista ai suoi genitori, mentre sua madre Patricia, dalla terrazza, chiedeva come mai non mi vedeva pi√π da quelle parti. 
Protagonista dell'intervista √® il buon Walter che, con l'aiuto di Fiammetta, ha parlato dell'attivit√† di cucina e della preparazione della salamoia per gli amici di Montechiaro, occupazioni che svolge sempre volentieri. L'intervista √® divertente e Walter, inizialmente un po' impacciato, vi ha partecipato con grande espressivit√† visiva e compiacimento.

• • • • • •
Breakfast for lunch üç¥. My morning was so busy that I’m only having breakfast now.
.
Super easy soft shell tacos with
1. Caramelized onions and peppers and mushrooms
2. Cheese and soft-scrambled eggs with a sprinkling of fresh parsley
3. Avo and cherry tomatoes 
.
.
#INGREDIENTS (Tacos)
1 cup Flour
1 TBSP Sugar
1/2 TSP Salt
1/2 TSP Baking Powder
1/2 Cup Warm Water
1/4 Cup Canola Oil
.
.
#METHOD
1. In a medium sized bowl, mix flour, salt, sugar & baking powder until well incorporated.
2. Create a well in your flour, pour in water and oil and combine until it forms a shaggy dough. 
3. Turn out dough into surface and knead for 5 minutes until it’s smooth. Rest for an hour (or overnight) 
4. Heat pan over meduim heat
5. Divided dough into 6 - 8 mini balls and shape into tacos using rolling pin
6. Put in hot pan and when bubbles for on surface, you’re ready to flip, cook for 30 more seconds. Repeat with remaining balls. 
7. Enjoy with whatever you like. 
.
.
.
.
.

#SpinnMovieSpot Weekend Review: AVA 

YEAR: 2020

GENRE: ACTION/THRILLER

MY REVIEW: As a huge Jessica Chastain fan, I'll have to admit this is the only movie she has done that I'll probably not be very eager to hype up.. The movie started quite well with good pace but dropped the pace as it progresses, the plot seem predictable and way too familiar, there is this lack of originality about it that seem to be eroding Hollywood of late, stories getting repackaged with different cast and directors.

Needless scenes and dialogues at some point.

Overall it is not an Exceptional or bad movie, it's just one of those movies you'll watch for thrills and "feel good"

Chastain in an action role felt weird as hell too.

I love Common as a rapper and sometimes as an actor, but after this movie he probably should take time off.

Overall it is not an Exceptional or bad movie, it's just one of those movies you'll watch for thrills and "feel good"

As lockdown restrictions are beginning to lift, going out starts to become normal again. Let's continue to care for our skin even on the go! Here are some of our must-haves on the go üí´ 

‚úÖStay hydrated by bringing water with you wherever you go in a reusable bottle. You should be aiming to drink at least 64 ounces (about 2 liters) of water a day! And remember, good skincare starts from within! 

‚úÖProtect yourself from UV rays! Always carry a sunscreen with a minimum of SPF 30 to protect yourself on the go. Having a travel size bottle on hand will make for easy transportation! 

‚úÖDon't neglect your lips! Keep chapped lips at bay by carrying a chapstick or lip balm with you. If you want a little glam, go for a tinted lip balm to add a little color while hydrating your lips!

‚úÖPack blotting sheets or a facial mist depending on your skin type! Blotting sheets are great for maintaining oil without over-washing or irrigating your face. 
A facial mist could be perfect to help bring some extra hydration or dewiness to your skin while you're out and about. 
Both methods are quick and easy fixes to maintain your skin when you are away from home!

node.text:
In 1928 the International Astronomical Union (IAU) determinedwhich constellations would be officially recognized. Of the 88 constellations on the IAU list, 48 were identified in ancient times with just the naked eye. The remaining 40 were added in more recent centuries.The IAU also defined each constellation's border so that the groupings represent not only star patterns but specific regions of the sky. These borders ensured that each star would be restricted to only one constellation. Constellations change over time the stars in them move through space. The dipper part of the Big Dipper in the constellation Ursa Major (Great Bear) appeared much more square in the past. Now the dipper's bowl is starting to elongate. About as 100,000 years from now, it will look
more like a soup bowl with a handle.

Happy Ganesh Chaturthi to you allüôè...
For the past one week I was hooked on to Amazon's webseries Breathe. Though the review was not good, I somehow liked both the seasons. Especially the second one. I find topics like multiple personality disorder very intriguing. The co existence of two personalities in the same body and one being completely unaware of the existence of the other. Thrilling. And though Abhishek Bachchan could never make it big I somehow always found him to be a nice actor. Comes across as a nice, classy gentleman and human being. Now I have to find another interesting webseries to keep me busy for something. Any suggestions most welcome ...
A kantha on Bangalore silk @dora_byphoenix and danglers to bring in the festive vibes !!...

node.text:
"Couch Queen"
.
--- ••• ---
VIRTUAL SHOOT

When this year started, I think, no one would have thought about the term Virtual Shoot. Then horror which we used to read in past came in reality for this generation... Pandemic. 
Lockdown was imposed in short interval notice and in a snap sound of fingers, many found themselves jobless, trapped inside. Privileged as me just had to get ourselves keep confined to our spaces. Real struggle was for them whose life started daily with sunrise and bread earned by long day hard work. Now there was no work.
As a photographers' perspective, shoots got cancelled, project delayed or denied. After a few days of not shooting, we started searching way to pursue passion. Business meetings started on conference video calls. Few photographers came with a temporary solution of shooting on video calls. Facetime shoots, WhatsApp Call shoots, Google video shoots, Skype shoot came in existence... in a shell, Virtual Shoots. Ofcourse not good as actual shoot, but "...dil ko khush rakhne ko ghalib ye khayal achchha hai...", it became a trend amongst photographers.
After initial denial, me too thought to give it a try. Talked to few people connected with me. Now I am sharing few results. 
I won't call myself as Photographer for these shots, just a director. 
--- ••• ---
In picture: @dikshadesire

shortcode_media.title: Keeley's Lockdown Rockdown #17: The Velvet Underground

node.text:
Here's a solo taster ahead of tonight's full band performance on Time Tunnel. The latest in a series of intimate one-off live performances from home is one of my favourite songs, Oh! Sweet Nuthin', closing track on The Velvet Underground's fourth album Loaded. Where the original was pure Country-Rock, I've taken it on a cosmic odyssey, reshaping it into a more spacious and even more sombre state.
It's the closest we can get to live performance at the moment...until tonight! Time Tunnel on Facebook from 9.30pm.

Here we present some brief insights about the vaccine development process.
